title:

text:
Shares of Alphabet Inc. Cl A 
        GOOGL,
        +0.04%
       shed 1.80% to $136.38 Wednesday, on what proved to be an all-around poor trading session for the stock market, with the S&P 500 Index 
        SPX,
        +0.11%
       falling 0.17% to 5,069.76 and Dow Jones Industrial Average 
        DJIA,
        +0.12%
       falling 0.06% to 38,949.02. Alphabet Inc. Cl A closed $17.40 short of its 52-week high ($153.78), which the company achieved on January 29th. The stock underperformed when compared to some of its competitors Wednesday, as Microsoft Corp. 
        MSFT,
        -0.17%
       rose 0.06% to $407.72, Amazon.com Inc. 
        AMZN,
        +0.31%
       fell 0.22% to $173.16, and Meta Platforms Inc. 
        META,
        -1.68%
       fell 0.62% to $484.02. Trading volume (36.0 M) eclipsed its 50-day average volume of 29.4 M.
